cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CY, cs.SE, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the design of a messaging protocol for a large scale IoT system. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the coordination and communication of real-world objects for efficient task performance. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper addresses the application of IoT in the context of smart grid for energy management. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper discusses the design and implementation of an IoT system using the XMPP protocol. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper discusses the backend server and cloud-enabled system for the IoT architecture.
